reviews.review_text: The energy will make you cry! I was 7 in 1979, but with tapes like this I can Go to Nassau and experience everything-the crowd goes berserk when they hear Franklin's, and the energy is a palpable wave throughout the first set.  But the sound is good, complemented not overshadowed by the crowd when it sings along with Tennessee Jed. Oh, and the jam after Saint is cosmic to say the least.  I teared up a couple of times, with a huge grin on my face, listening to this for the first time.
